The '1992–93 FA Cup' was the 112th season of the FA Cup, also known as
'The Football Association Challenge Cup'. It was won by Arsenal, who beat
Sheffield Wednesday 2–1 in the replay after a 1–1 draw in the final
at the old Wembley Stadium. The goals were scored by Ian Wright and Andy
Linighan, who scored in the 119th minute.
